            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-[#0077B6] mb-4">The Engineering of a Yacht Propeller</h1>
            <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-[#004D74]">A Data-Driven Look at Sand Casting Nickel-Aluminium Bronze</p>
        </header>

        <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 lg:gap-8 my-10">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#00A1E4] mb-4">The Challenge</h2>
                <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
                    Ship propellers operate in one of the planet's harshest environments. They must withstand immense mechanical stress, high rotational speeds, and constant exposure to corrosive seawater. Manufacturing them requires exceptional dimensional accuracy and material integrity to ensure efficiency and prevent catastrophic failure.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#00A1E4] mb-4">The Solution: NAB Casting</h2>
                <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
                    For this Ø420 mm yacht propeller, sand casting with **Nickel-Aluminium Bronze (NAB, C95800)** is the optimal solution. This process allows for the complex 4-blade geometry, while NAB provides a superior combination of strength, castability, and outstanding resistance to both corrosion and cavitation erosion.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="my-10 md:my-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#0077B6] mb-8">Propeller Key Specifications</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 md:gap-6">
                <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-xl p-6 text-center">
                    <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-[#00A1E4]">Ø420<span class="text-3xl">mm</span></div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-semibold mt-2">Overall Diameter</div>
                </div>
